block content

  +state('Utah', '/assets/images/flag-utah.svg', 'The Beehive State', 'January 4, 1896')

  .intro
    p In prepration for the 1903 St. Louis World’s Fair, the Utah Daughters of the American Revolution (DAR) created an unofficial flag. It was embroidered by Agnes Frenelius of Zion’s Cooperative Mercantile Institution.
    p The flag, a field of blue with the coat of arms in white, was officially adopted March 9, 1911.
    p In 1913, a full color version was adopted.
    p In 1922, Dollie McMonegal embroidered the flag with an error (the year 1947 was moved outside of the shield). This was copied and reproduced for years, until the error was noticed and corrected.
    p This corrected version was adopted February 16, 2011.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Utah flag features a field of blue charged with the state coat of arms, centered.
      p The year 1896 is inscribed below the coat of arms and both are surrounded by a gold ring.
      +survey('Utah', '58th')
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah-icon-eagle.svg')
          h4 eagle
          p freedom, strength, the United States
        li.icon-item
