  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p Utah statutes do not specify dimensions or proportion for the flag.
      p A 1909 correspondence between Wm. H. Horstmann Co. and National Guard Adjutant General Edgar A. Wedgewood specified the flag be 52 inches by 66 inches.
      p It is often produced with these dimensions or with a 3:5 proportion.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah-dimensions.svg')

  .guide.wide.timeline
    .content
      h2 Previous iterations
      ul.visual.flag-list
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah-1903-1913.jpg')
          h4 1903–1913
          p The original DAR flag, adopted in 1911.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah-1913-2011.jpg')
          h4 1913–2011
          p The coat of arms is changed to full color, encircled with gold. The incorrect McMonegal version is shown here.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah-2011-prototype.jpg')
          h4 2011–Present
          p A prototype design by the Colonial Flag Company.
        li.flag-item
          span.flag: img(src='/assets/images/flag-utah.svg')
          h4 2011–Present
          p An enhanced version of the 2011 prototype created by Perry Van Schelt. This or the prototype version can be used.

